			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Guide to Augmenting is as follows.
<br />

<br />
1) Get yourself an augment. Drop randomly in LDoN dungeons of all mobs or can be bought at the LDoN merchnt (HINT- the one with "Adventure Merchant" below their name).
<br />

<br />
2) Get look at the aug and determine, (A) 2 things. What slot it fits in (1-8, or all), and (B) what if any restrictions it has on it.
<br />

<br />
3) Get your favorite item that has the slot that maches the aug and meetes the restrictions on the aug.
<br />

<br />
4) Go to one of the adventure camps. anyone will do. In each there is an aug pool. It actually looks like a little bird bath. when you click on it it will open a 2 slot container. Put the aug and the itme in it and hit combine. You will be given back the item that now sats AUGMENTED after the name of it and upon investigation will show the aug's name next to the slot on the item.
<br />

<br />
Guide to Aug pools...
<br />

<br />
These things are small and annoying to find. This is a better detailed location of where they are at each camp
<br />

<br />

<br />
1) Everfrost - In the little building thing wihtout a roof. Right smack in the center of it.
<br />

<br />
2) Butcherblock - Look for the Wagon cart. It is just on the otherside of that next to the tent.
<br />

<br />
3)East Commonlands - Behind the camp near the back of the cave.
<br />

<br />
4) South Ro (?) -Between two of the tents.
<br />

<br />
5) North Ro - Honestly I have no idea. Never been there.
<br />

<br />

<br />
A couple of notes on this subject as well.  Be very careful when augmenting. An aug that says it fits in all slots will automatically fill the first slot open on an item. So if your item has a SLOT 1 and a SLOT 7, and you have an aug for a SLOT 1 and an aug for any slot. you need to use the SLOT type 1 aug first then the any, as the ANY if used first will go into the Type 1 slot. Alos, augs can be removed. However, the aug is destroyed when you do this. To do this go to the Magus at each camop and click on them like you would a merchant. They sell 3 kinds of Solvents. Slot 1,2, and 3. No item will have more than 3 slots on it. Just buy the solvent for the slot you want to remove an aug from and combine it and the item in the pool. Also an augged item is NO DROP. This is very handy on PvP servers as you can make all your good droppable gear NO DROP and not have to worry about bagging your gear when you travel. 
<br />

<br />
One thing to be aware of if you play on a PvP server. Be very careful when trying to aug something. I lost a +10 HP aug when I was attacked with the aug in the pool and I backed up out of the camp with out thnking.  I have seen it many times as well.  The camps are a PKs heaven. So beware.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.synthea.com/pansig%20copy.jpg" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
<a href="https://www.synthea.com" target="_blank" class="postlink"> Art by Synthea </a>
